Body: Description: In our environment we have a domain controller located at our office in the UK and we have StealthBits configured in line to the main Domain Controller in us data center. We have a solution in place to do remote scanning as we do not have an agent on the UK domain controller.  I believe the set up we have now is out of date and there is a better way to be doing this.  Is there any documentation you can share for better ways to do this remote scanning?

Netwrix Enterprise Auditor v11.6 > Requirements > File System Solution > File System Supported Platforms Windows File Server Target Requirements > Windows File Server Access & Sensitive Data Auditing Configuration https://helpcenter.netwrix.com/bundle/EnterpriseAuditor_11.6/page/Content/Config/WindowsFile/Access.htm#windows_file_system_clusters

 

Scanning Windows File System Clusters

The following information outlines specific configurations required for performing FSAA, FSAC, and SDD scans:

  • For FSAA and SDD scans, configure a custom host list to target the cluster's Role Server.
  • For FSAC scans, configure a custom host list to target the Windows File Server Cluster.

The host targeted by the File System scans is only the host entry for the cluster. For example:

The environment has a Windows File System Cluster named ExampleCluster1 with three nodes named ExampleNodeA, ExampleNodeB, and ExampleNodeC. There would be four host entries in the StealthAUDIT Master Host Table: ExampleCluster1, ExampleNodeA, ExampleNodeB, and ExampleNodeC. Each of these four entries would have the same value of the cluster name in the WinCluster column: ExampleCluster1. Only the ExampleCluster1 host would be in the host list targeted by the File System scans.

 

The File System Activity Scan > Activity Settings Page > Host Mapping option in the File System Access Auditor Data Collector Wizard in StealthAUDIT provides a method for mapping between the target host and the hosts where activity logs reside. However, this feature requires advanced SQL scripting knowledge to build the query.

 

To create custom host lists for File System scans, see the StealthAUDIT Connection Profile & Host List topic for additional information.
